    <item>
      <title>The Unyielding Envy of Krodhishva</title>
      <description>Today&apos;s story will change how you see everything... In the kingdom of Anga, a young warrior named Krodhishva emerged as a prodigy, surpassing even the greatest heroes of the land. His prowess in battle was unmatched, and his name became synonymous with valor. But as Krodhishva&apos;s fame grew, so did the envy of his peers. They saw how their king, King Vrisha, favored him above all others, and they began to resent Krodhishva&apos;s privileged position. They whispered among themselves, &apos;Why should he have all the glory?&apos; &apos;Why should he be the chosen one?&apos; Their malice simmered beneath the surface, awaiting the perfect moment to strike. That moment came when Krodhishva&apos;s king entrusted him with a vital mission to defeat the neighboring kingdom. The enemy lines were strong, but Krodhishva&apos;s skills were unmatched. He led the charge, cutting down enemy warriors with ease. But as he reached the heart of the enemy camp, he saw a vision of himself, standing triumphantly, with the enemy king at his feet. The vision consumed him, and he became blinded by his own ambition. He saw his peers, his friends, and even his king as obstacles to be eliminated. His envy boiled over, and he turned against his own allies, slaughtering them without mercy. When the battle was won, Krodhishva returned to his king, but his heart was heavy with the weight of his own actions. He realized too late that envy had consumed him, and that his greatest enemy was not the enemy king, but his own insatiable ambition. This is Envy — the green-eyed monster that destroys even the greatest of heroes. Today we compete, we compare, we covet. Ask yourself, what is the cost of your own envy?</description>
